# Verification tiers gate (T0 / T1 / T2)

Canonical doc: `docs/VERIFICATION-TIERS.md` in the consuming umbraculum-class repo (e.g. umbraculum-dev).

## Rule (hard)

After editing **`apps/**`**, **`services/**`**, or **`packages/**`** (non-doc-only):

1. **Before declaring done:** run **T0 or T1** via skill **`verify-slice-runbook`** (named slice or `--from-diff`).
2. **Before push:** run **T2-PR** — `npm run verify:pre-push` (skill **`path-aware-pre-push`**) or **T2-release** — `npm run verify:pre-push:release` when manifest/pins/SDK tags change.

## Anti-patterns

- Do **not** run `./scripts/build-packages-in-docker.sh` for a single-package `src/` edit when `./scripts/build-package-in-docker.sh @umbraculum/<name> --include-dependents` suffices.
- Do **not** treat T1 green as T2 green.
- Do **not** use host `npm test` in containerized repos.

## Skills

| Tier | Skill |
|------|-------|
| T0/T1 | `verify-slice-runbook`, `scoped-package-build-in-docker` |
| T2-PR | `path-aware-pre-push`, `ci-parity-local-reproduction` |
| T2-release | `ci-parity-local-reproduction` (`--full`) |
| T2 API | auto from T2-PR; else `api-integration-tests-pre-push` |
